Bindraban, P.S. and Rabbinge, R. 2004. Technologies That Can Make A Difference: Enhancing Agricultural Productivity in Africa. InterAcademy of Sciences, Washington, D.C., USA.<br/> <a href="http://www.interacademycouncil.net/CMS/Reports/AfricanAgriculture/PDFs.aspx?returnID=7807" target="_blank">http://www.interacademycouncil.net/CMS/Reports/AfricanAgriculture/PDFs.aspx?returnID=7807</a></p><p>Dorward, A., Kydd, J., Morrison, J. and Urey, I. 2004. A policy agenda for pro-poor agricultural growth. <i>World Development </i>32: 73-89.</p><p>Echeverría, R.G. and Beintema, N.M. 2009. Mobilizing financial resources for agricultural research in developing countries: Trends and mechanisms. Global Forum for Agricultural Research. Rome, Italy. <a href="http://www.fao.org/docs/eims/upload/261898/mobilizing%20financial%20resources%20for%20AR4D.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.fao.org/docs/eims/upload/261898/mobilizing%20financial%20resources%20for%20AR4D.pdf</a></p><p>Evenson, R.E. 2001. Economic impacts of agricultural research and extension. In Gardner, B.L. and Rausser, G.C. (Eds). <i>Handbook of Agricultural Economics</i>, <i>Volume 1A: Agricultural Production</i>. Elsevier, New York, USA, pp. 573-628.</p><p>IAC. 2004. Realizing the Promise and Potential of African Agriculture: Science and Technology Strategies for Improving Agricultural Productivity and Food Security in Africa. IAC (InterAcademy Council), Amsterdam, Netherlands. <a href="http://www.interacademycouncil.net/?id=9989%20" target="_blank">http://www.interacademycouncil.net/?id=9989 </a></p><p>Kerr, J. and Kolavalli, S. 1999. Impact of Agricultural Research on Poverty Alleviation: Conceptual Framework with Illustrations from the Literature. EPTD Discussion Paper No. 56. International Food Policy Research Institute. Washington D.C., USA.<a href="http://impact.cgiar.org/sites/default/files/KerrKolavalli1999.pdf" target="_self"> http://impact.cgiar.org/sites/default/files/KerrKolavalli1999.pdf</a></p><p>Maredia, M.K